headline: 3 Reasons to Sell VTRS and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Viatris’s 35.8% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 8.4%, and its stock price has climbed to $10.44 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
